latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Apple Cinnamon Tea Time Cake - Sugar Free & Made With Whole Wheat 
.
Do try this yummy cake for Christmas & do share your feedback 😍
.
Preparation Time - 10 min
Baking Time - 40 mins
Serves - 8 Slices 
.
Ingredients 
Whole Wheat Flour - 1 Cup
Baking Powder - 1 tsp
Baking Soda - 1/2 tsp
Cinnamon Powder - 1 tsp
Cocoa Powder - 2 tbsp
Apple - 1
Oil/ Butter - 1/4 Cup
Jaggery - 1/2 Cup tightly packed 
Milk - 3/4 Cup
Vanilla Essence - 1 tsp
Dry Fruits & Nuts - as per choice 
.
Steps
➡️ Take a mixing bowl and Sift together Whole Wheat Flour,  baking powder,  soda , Cinnamon and Cocoa Powder and keep aside. 
➡️ Blend together peeled Apple,  milk, oil and jaggery to make puree.
➡️ Use chopped nuts of your choice and dust them once with dry flour as shown in the video. 
➡️ Add Puree to dry ingredients along with vanilla essence .
➡️ Use cut & fold method to mix the batter. Do not over mix.
➡️ Pre heat oven @170 degrees for 15 minutes. 
➡️ Grease Baking tin with oil and line using butter paper.
➡️ Pour batter and garnish nuts. Tap the tin few times.
➡️ Bake for 35-40 mins. Let the cake cool down completely before you slice it.
➡️ Consume within 2 days or store in refrigerator and use upto a week.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Ganesh Chaturthi Recipe Series
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ganesh Chaturthi Special 
Recipe 3
Sindhi Style Aata Ladoo
.
Preparation Time - 10 mins
Cooking Time - 20 mins 
Serves - 10 ladoos
INGREDIENTS 
Gond/ Edible Gum - 1 tbsp 
Whole Wheat Flour - 2 Cups
Oil - 3/4 Cup + 2 tbsp
Almonds - 1 tbsp
Cashew - 1 tbsp
Walnuts - 1 tbsp
Raisins - 1 tbsp
Dryfruit Mix - 2 tbsp for coating ladoos
Powdered Sugar - 1 Cup
Cardamom Powder - 1 tbsp
.
Steps
➡️ Heat oil in a pan.  Fry gond on medium flame for 2 minutes.  Keep aside and crush it once cool.
➡️ In the same Oil add aata and saute for 10-12 mins on low to medium flame.  Keep stirring continuously. 
➡️ Add cardamom powder and continue cooking for 2 mins.
➡️ Add dry fruits and crushed gond and give it a mix. Cook for 1 minutes and switch off the flame. 
➡️ Add powdered sugar and mix it well. Let the ladoo mix cool for sometime. 
➡️ Mix It with hands once and give shape of ladoos when still warm.
➡️ Coat ladoos with dry fruit mix and keep aside for 1 hour before consuming. 
➡️ Can be stored upto a month if stored in a air tight container.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Ganesh Chaturthi Special Recipes
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ganesh Chaturthi Special 
Recipe 2
Instant Mawa Modak - 2 Ways 
.
Preparation Time - 5 Mins
Cooking Time - 15 Mins
Serves - 12 Modaks
.
Ingredients 
Mix Dry Fruits - 4 tbsp
Tutti Fruiti - 1 tsp ( Optional)
Choco Chips - 1 tbsp
Desiccated Coconut - 1 tbsp
Ghee - 2 tsp
Milk - 1/2 cup
Milk Powder - 1 cup
Powdered Sugar - 1/2 cup
Cardamom Powder - 1/2 tsp
For Chocolate Modak
Cocoa Powder - 1.5 tsp
Powdered Sugar - 1/2 tsp
Water - 4 tsp
.
Steps 
➡️ Dry roast dry fruits for 2 minutes on low flame.  Transfer to a bowl.
➡️ Add tutti fruiti, choco chips, desiccated coconut and mix it well. Modak filling is ready. 
➡️ Heat ghee in a pan. Add milk and mix it well. Add milk powder and mix it continuously and keep the flame medium.
➡️ Once milk powder is mixed add Powdered sugar and mix it well.
➡️ After 7-8 mins the mixture will turn thick.  Add cardamom powder and cook until mawa doesn't stick to the pan.
➡️ Transfer to bowl.  Once little cool. Divide into 2 parts. 
➡️ Make chocolate mixture as shown in the video and add to one part of mawa and mix it well.  Keep in fridge for 5 mins to set it nicely. 
➡️ Use modak mould and add a layer of mawa and filling in the center and another layer of mawa on top. You can also make modak without mould as shown in the video. 
➡️ Best option for ganesh pooja bhog or prasad.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Sindhi Style Meya Patata Recipe
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Sindhi Style Meya Patata Recipe 
.
Meya means Tinde or Apple Gourd and patata means Potato. This is a famous Sindhi Curry made using garlic,  coriander leaves and green chilli.  We call it Thoom Masala ( Green Gravy). This goes best with rice as well as roti.
.
Meya Patata
Preparation Time - 10 mins
Cooking Time - 25 mins
Serves - 4
.
INGREDIENTS 
Meya - 3
Potato - 1 big or 2 small
Coriander Leaves - 2 cups
Green Chilli - 2
Garlic - 15 
Mustard Oil - 4 tbsp 
Salt to taste 
Turmeric Powder - 1 tsp
Coriander Powder - 1.5 tbsp
Tomato - 2 medium 
Water - 1.5 cups
.
Steps
➡️ Peel and cut meya and aloo in equal size. 
➡️ Coarse grind coriander leaves,  garlic and chilli. 
➡️ Heat oil in a pan. Add green masala. Cook for 2 minutes.  Add salt, turmeric and coriander powder.  Saute for 2 minutes on medium flame. 
➡️ Add tomatoes and mix everything well. Pressure cook for 2 whistles on medium flame. 
➡️ Saute the masala for few minutes.  Mash it well.
➡️ Add meya and aloo, mix it well with masala. Saute for few minutes or until oil separates. 
➡️ Add Water and check salt. Cook for 2 whistles and 2 minutes on low. Flame should be medium. 
➡️ Let pressure release on its own.
➡️ Serve with roti or rice.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Soft & Puffed Indian Phulka /Roti Recipe
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Indian Phulka Recipe - Soft & Puffed On Tawa
.
Check out the detailed Phulka Recipe video from scratch with tips and tricks to make perfect soft and puffy phulka everytime.
.
Preparation Time - 20 mins 
Cooking Time - 20 mins
Serves -  15 Phulkas
.
INGREDIENTS 
Whole Wheat Flour - 2 cups
Water - 3/4 cup approx
Oil - 1/2 tsp
Ghee - as required 
.
Steps 
➡️ Take a mixing bowl, add aata and knead with water.  Dough should be semi soft. Knead it for 2-3 minutes and make it smooth. It should not stick to hand. Add 1/2 tsp oil and make dough smooth.
➡️ Cover & rest the dough 10 mins.
➡️ After 10 mins, knead it once again and make small dough balls( I made 15 phulkas)
➡️ Use dry flour to roll the phulka thin. 
➡️ Tawa should be medium hot. After placing phulka when you see small bubbles,  flip the phulka. 
➡️ Completely cook other side on medium flame by rotating it. And the flip the other side .
➡️ Apply slight pressure using spatula or cloth, so that phulka is puffed up.
➡️ Apply ghee and immediately store in a casserole.
➡️ Never keep phulka or roti without covering as it will make it hard & dry.
.

I started my content journey 5 years ago — during those uncertain days after the COVID lockdown.

After working with some of the biggest names like TCS and Reliance, life took a different turn. I left behind my career, my work identity… and embraced the beautiful yet demanding role of a homemaker and a mother.

But deep down, there was always a void. A quiet voice whispering that something was missing — something that was mine.

I started posting on Instagram, just hoping to share a part of my everyday life. Honestly, I lacked all the confidence. I didn’t feel fancy, cool, or “talented enough” like so many amazing content creators out there.
I used to think — “Who’s going to watch my videos?”
But still, I showed up.

And you — all of you — proved me wrong in the most beautiful way.

Today, I held the YouTube Silver Play Button in my hands.
And it hit me…
This isn’t just a milestone.
This is a reminder of every step, every doubt, every moment I thought of quitting… and every single one of you who chose to believe in me.

Your support, your love, your constant encouragement — it gave me the courage I never thought I had.

From being a hesitant mom filming in her kitchen… to someone who now proudly owns her space on the internet — this journey has been nothing short of magic. ✨

Thank you for giving me this second innings in life.
Thank you for 100K+ on YouTube.
Thank you for 700K hearts on Instagram.
Thank you for making me believe in myself again.

This Silver Button belongs to all of us. 🩶

Masoor Dal Beetroot Oats Dosa

Healthy skin & body start from within 🌿
It takes time and effort, but it’s always worth it — like today’s Masoor Dal & Oats Dosa loaded with veggies 

Recipe Guided by my Dietitian @enrich_lifestyle_with_urvi

Ingredients 
Masoor Dal 1 Cup
Oats 1/4 Cup
Green Chilli 2
Ginger 1 Inch
Jeera 1/2 tbsp
Beetroot 1 Small
Onion 1/2
Salt to taste 
For Filling 
Ghee 1tsp
Vegetables 1 Cup
Paneer 60 grams
Salt 1/4 tsp
Podi Masala 1tbsp
Red Chilli 1tsp
Steps
➡️ Soak Masoor Dal for 4-5 hours. Transfer to blender along with other ingredients  mentioned above. 
➡️ Add some water if required. Transfer batter to a bowl. Add salt and mix it well.
➡️ For Filling saute some Paneer and veggies of your choice in Ghee. 
➡️ Add spices and cook for 2 mins.
➡️ Make dosa and add this Stuffing. Serve with any Chutney of your choice.
